1a7ebc5" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" s=
tyle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wid=
th: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgrou=
nd-color: #ccc;">  I wrote a column</a> about how the board made and descri=
bed that decision. What was striking, to me, was that Twitter=E2=80=99s the=
n-CEO, Parag Agrawal, described the decision to sell as=C2=A0<em>purely=C2=
=A0</em>doing what was in the best interests of shareholders, without any c=
onsideration of the product, the mission, the employees, etc. Agrawal <a hr=
ef=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33537957.286427/aHR0cHM=
6Ly93d3cucGxhdGZvcm1lci5uZXdzL3AvaW5zaWRlLXR3aXR0ZXJzLWVtb3Rpb25hbC1mcmlkYX=
k/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB2daa0119" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"it=
emscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !=
important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-b=
ottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> said to employees</a>:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThis is the answer you do=
n=E2=80=99t want to hear, right?=E2=80=9D Agrawal said. =E2=80=9CTwitter is=
 a public company owned by shareholders. There are other companies which ma=
y have other legal mechanics =E2=80=A6 Twitter is not one of those companie=
s.=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That is partly true, but not entirely true, an=
d kind of grim. I wrote:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A lot of people think of Twitter a=
s a public utility, a public trust, =E2=80=9Cthe town square,=E2=80=9D a co=
mpany with an important social mission that many of its users and employees=
=C2=A0<em>and Elon Musk=C2=A0</em>care about deeply. And its CEO and board =
of directors essentially can=E2=80=99t bring themselves to talk about it. W=
hen employees asked him about what was best for the company, Agrawal could =
talk only about the shareholders. Elon Musk is not at all embarrassed to sa=
y that Twitter has an important public mission, which is why he=E2=80=99s b=
uying it. But its current management can=E2=80=99t say that, which is why t=
hey=E2=80=99re selling it.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And now the chairman of the Twitter board that=
 sold to Musk is the chairman of OpenAI. Which definitely=C2=A0<em>does=C2=
=A0</em>have other legal mechanics. For now.</p>
